Program: The History Hour
Title: The Man Who Inspired Britain's First Aids Charity
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqmh
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 4 Dec 2018
The first man in Britain to die of AIDS, whale hunting in the South Atlantic in the 1950s, how Norway voted not to join the EU, the American adventurer who inspired the Indiana Jones stories, and Saddam Hussein's draining of Iraq's southern marshes in a bid to flush out his opponents. Picture: Terrence Higgins (Courtesy: Dr Rupert Whitaker) Show less